The paper deals with approximation algorithms for the Steiner Tree problem, which is a well-studied problem in computer science. The paper presents a unified view of these algorithms based on star contractions, which is a common technique used in many of these algorithms. Therefore, the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
